                                <div class="padding-bottom padding-small">
                                    <div class="body-medium text-indent text-color-clay w-richtext">
                                        <p>Kofi has over three decades of senior leadership experience in both private and public entities from telecommunications, marketing research, sectoral regulations and consulting. He was the Director of Regulatory Administration at the National Communications Authority (NCA) for ten (10) years until he retired in May 2025. He served as an adjunct lecturer at the Ghana Telecommunications University College where he taught Telecoms Policy and Regulations at the graduate school for thirteen years and in the past reviewed articles for the Emerald.<br><br>
                                            At the NCA, he supervised regulatory functions such as market regulation, licensing, standards &amp; conformance, quality of service monitoring among others. Some of the key regulatory works he supervised while at the NCA includes the setting of Wholesale Interconnect Rates (WIR), review and update of Tower Installation and Maintenance Guidelines for the telecommunications industry, Significant Market Power study in conjunction with Analysis Mason, the merger of Airtel Ghana and TiGo Ghana, acquisition of majority shares in Ghana Telecommunications Company Limited by Telecel. Kofi also led the team that worked with KPMG Ghana to successfully execute the first spectrum auction in the telecommunication industry in Ghana.<br><br>
                                            Prior to public service, Kofi worked at a number of private entities like Research International Ghana, Africa Online Ghana and DiscoveryTel Ghana. At Research International, he managed all ad hoc international research and continuous marketing research jobs for entities like Coca Cola International, British Broadcasting Corporation, Shell International, Unilever Ghana and Guinness Ghana to mention a few. As the General Manager of DiscoveryTel Ghana, he worked with the team to successfully implement the first 4G Wireless Network in Ghana using WiMAX 16e technology.<br><br>
                                            He currently serves on the Board of Safety Insurance Brokers Limited as Board Chairman and People&rsquo;s Pension Trust as a member of the Board. Apart from managing the Competition &amp; Markets Center, he consults for a number of companies.<br><br>
                                            Kofi has a number of post graduate qualifications; a Master&rsquo;s degree in Communications Management (MCM) from the University of Strathclyde Management School and an LL.M in Information Technology and Telecommunications Law from the same University. Additionally, he holds an LL.M in Competition Law and Economics from the Brussels School of Competition/Li&egrave;ge. He has post graduate diplomas from King&rsquo;s College; one in EU Competition Law and the other in Economics for Competition Law.</p>
                                    </div>
